The paper discusses a novel mini-batch selection strategy for training neural network architectures, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions experiments on standard datasets related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), indicating that the proposed method can be applied to various domains. Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization problem and algorithmic approach, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the generalization performance of the proposed method, which is a key aspect of neural network training and falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
